<task id="062" project="ai-procedure-quality-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build scripts/quality/Test-ReferenceExemplars.ps1 exemplar harness</title>
    <phase>4a</phase>
    <stream>infrastructure</stream>
    <tags>validator, exemplar, ci</tags>
    <estimate>1-2h</estimate>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <parallel-group>4a-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>005, 028</dependencies>
    <writes-to>scripts/quality/</writes-to>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>For each skill with opted-in `exemplar:` frontmatter, rebuild the exemplar with the skill's prescribed command and verify output matches committed reference within 20% tolerance.</goal>
    <context>Today's bundle regression (SDV 440 KB → 6.7 MB) would have been caught by this. Skills with `exemplar: none-too-volatile` are SKIPPED — that's the opt-out per resolved decision #4.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Runtime: variable (depends on # opted-in exemplars and build time). NOT a pre-commit candidate; runs nightly or on PR.
      - Must NOT run on every commit — too slow for the &lt;30s GHA budget
      - Reads .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md frontmatter; skips skills without `exemplar:` or with `exemplar: none-too-volatile`
      - For each opted-in: parse the skill's prescribed build command, run it, compare bundle.js size against committed reference (within 20%)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-SKILLS.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/inventory/pcf-bundle-baseline.json</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Walk .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md; parse frontmatter for `exemplar:` field</step>
    <step>For each opted-in: identify the skill's prescribed build command (per its body) + the reference file (the committed bundle.js or equivalent)</step>
    <step>For each opted-in: run the build (npm run build:prod or similar); capture output file size</step>
    <step>Compare against committed reference; flag if deviation &gt; 20%</step>
    <step>Report: PASS/FAIL per skill, with deviation details for FAILs</step>
    <step>Output JSON report at .claude/QUALITY-EXEMPLAR-LAST.json (consumed by audit skill)</step>
    <step>Exit non-zero on any FAIL</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output>scripts/quality/Test-ReferenceExemplars.ps1</output>
    <output>.claude/QUALITY-EXEMPLAR-LAST.json (output produced when run)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Runs successfully against all opted-in exemplars</criterion>
    <criterion>Skips opted-out exemplars (rationale noted in output)</criterion>
    <criterion>Test case with deliberately-bloated bundle (run `npm run build` instead of `build:prod` for SDV) returns FAIL with actionable diff</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
